{"article_id":"q4XxvHxH5PDJQSHP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The partial shutdown of the US government has become the longest ever ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"with no end in sight to the political standoff .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"On Saturday it reaches its 22nd day ,","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"overtaking the previous record","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"- the 21-day shutdown in 1995-96 under then-President Bill Clinton .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"President Donald Trump is refusing to approve a budget","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"unless it includes funds for a wall on the Mexican border .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"About a quarter of the federal government is still out of operation","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"until a spending plan is agreed ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"leaving 800,000 employees unpaid .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"On Friday , those workers","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"- including prison guards , airport staff and FBI agents -","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"missed their first salaries of the year .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Meanwhile , President Trump has calmed speculation","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"that he is about to declare a national emergency","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"in order to bypass Congress","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and get the money","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"he needs .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"His proposed border wall was a key election pledge .","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"He described an emergency declaration as an `` easy way out ''","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"he would prefer Congress to resolve the problem .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"But he added :","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"`` If they ca n't do it ...","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"I will declare a national emergency .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"I have the absolute right . ''","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Correspondents say","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Democrats would mount an immediate legal challenge","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"if Mr Trump made such a move .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"On Friday , some workers","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"who missed their first payday of the year","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"shared their blank payslips on social media .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"Oscar Murillo , an aerospace engineer at Nasa , posted his $ 0 cheque on Twitter","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"he had actually lost money","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"because of mandatory deductions .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Another Twitter user , Cat Heifner , shared what she said","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"was her brother 's payslip ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"showing","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"he had been paid one cent for his work as an air traffic controller .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"A food bank in Washington DC is arranging five pop-up markets on Saturday for unpaid federal workers .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Radha Muthiah , head of Capital Area Food Bank , said","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"dozens of volunteers were working","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"to pack bags of food for affected staff .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Meanwhile , the classified advertising website Craigslist has been inundated with listings from government employees","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"trying to sell their possessions .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Items ranging from beds to old toys","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"have been listed as `` government shutdown specials '' .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"`` Sells for $ 93.88 at Walmart .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Asking $ 10 , ''","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"one advert for a child 's rocking chair reads .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"`` We need money","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"to pay bills . ''","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"Of the 800,000 federal employees","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"going unpaid ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"about 350,000 are furloughed","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"- a kind of temporary lay-off -","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"while the rest are continuing to work .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Thousands have reportedly applied for unemployment benefits amid the financial uncertainty .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"One major airport , Miami International , will close an entire terminal this weekend","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"because of a shortage of security agents","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"caused by the shutdown .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"The agents are `` essential '' federal workers","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"and expected to work -","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"despite not being paid","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"until the shutdown ends .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"Instead many agents are calling in sick in protest at the situation ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"the Miami Herald reports .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"The House and Senate overwhelmingly passed a bill on Friday","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to ensure","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"all government workers receive retroactive pay","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"after the shutdown ends .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"The president is expected to sign the legislation .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"But that may be small consolation to those federal employees currently in dire straits , with no end in sight to the impasse .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"At a roundtable discussion about border security on Friday with state and local leaders , Mr Trump again demanded","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"that Democrats approve funding for a wall or steel barrier .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"However , the Democratic leader of the US House of Representatives said","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"the ball was in Mr Trump 's court .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"Speaker Nancy Pelosi told reporters :","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"`` When the president acts ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"we will respond to whatever he does . ''","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"According to the Associated Press ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"senior White House aide Jared Kushner","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"- Mr Trump 's son-in-law -","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"is among those","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"who have cautioned the president against declaring a national emergency .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"US media report","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"the White House is considering diverting some of the $ 13.9bn","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"allocated last year by Congress for disaster relief in such areas as Puerto Rico , Texas and California","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"to pay for the wall .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"But Republican congressman Mark Meadows ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"who is close to the president ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that option was not under serious consideration .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Please include a contact number","depth":4},{"id":95,"text":"if you are willing to speak to a BBC journalist .","depth":4},{"id":96,"text":"You can also contact us in the following ways :","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":193,"left":101,"right":192,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":101,"left":98,"right":100,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":2,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":192,"left":189,"right":191,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":189,"left":124,"right":188,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":108,"right":123,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":108,"left":102,"right":107,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":104,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":103,"right":9,"relation":"causal","nuclearity